## 10 · EU AI Act compliance architecture

- **Art. 9 risk management** — risk register at `audit/risk_register.md`, reviewed each milestone.
- **Art. 10 data governance** — lineage tracked in `tracking/data_lineage.jsonl`.
- **Art. 11 technical documentation** — this file + `SPEC.md` + `audit/audit_sheet.xlsx`.
- **Art. 12 record-keeping** — `tracking/sessions/*` + structured logs retained {{retention_period}}.
- **Art. 13/50 transparency** — user-facing notice template at `tools/prompts/user_disclosure.md`.
- **Art. 14 human oversight** — HITL gates at every session checkpoint + `<70%` confidence trigger.
- **Art. 15 accuracy / robustness / cybersecurity** — see NFR-001..006 in `SPEC.md`.
- **Art. 17 quality management** — `audit/audit_sheet.xlsx` + checklists at `audit/checklists/`.
- **Art. 72 post-market monitoring** — `tracking/post_market_monitor.jsonl` + alerts.
- **Art. 73 incident management** — runbook at `docs/runbooks/incident.md`.

## 11 · Anti-patterns explicitly avoided

- Mock-based testing of integration points where real DB / API is feasible (AIE-021 prevention).
- Single-LLM-vendor lock at orchestration level (P1).
- Silent defaults on schema validation (P2 / AIE-013 prevention).
- Hardcoded dates / versions in templates (P5 / AIE-030 prevention).
- Premature abstraction (rule: 3 similar lines is better than a premature interface).

## 12 · Versioning + rollback

